To secure an AWS VPC using IAM policies, you can use the `ec2:Vpc` condition key to specify the full ARN of the VPC. For example, to allow a specific instance to view resources in other AWS services within a specific VPC, you can attach a policy with the following statement:

```
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": "*",
      "Resource": "*",
      "Condition": {
        "StringLike": {
          "ec2:Vpc": "arn:aws:ec2:*:*:vpc/vpc-ec43eb89"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

[Source: aws/EC2/Example policies for working with the AWS CLI or an AWS SDK<a name="ExamplePolicies_EC2"></a> > Example: Allow a specific instance to view resources in other AWS services<a name="iam-example-source-instance"></a>]

To secure an AWS VPC using IAM policies, you can create a policy that grants users permission to add and remove inbound and outbound rules for any security group in a specific VPC. This is achieved by specifying the `ec2:Vpc` condition key to specify that these actions can only be performed on security groups in a specific VPC [Source: aws/EC2/Policy structure<a name="iam-policy-structure"></a> > Condition keys for Amazon EC2<a name="amazon-ec2-keys"></a>] .

For example, the following policy grants users permission to add and remove inbound and outbound rules for any security group in a specific VPC:
```
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "ec2:AuthorizeSecurityGroupIngress",
        "ec2:AuthorizeSecurityGroupEgress",
        "ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupIngress",
        "ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupEgress"
      ],
      "Resource": "*",
      "Condition": {
        "StringLike": {
          "ec2:Vpc": ["vpc-12345678"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```
This policy uses the `ec2:Vpc` condition key to specify that these actions can only be performed on security groups in a specific VPC (`vpc-12345678`).

Additionally, you can create an IAM role and policy that grants users permissions to enable or disable a VPC for ClassicLink, link or unlink an instance to a ClassicLink-enabled VPC, and to view ClassicLink-enabled VPCs and linked EC2-Classic instances [Source: aws/EC2/ClassicLink<a name="vpc-classiclink"></a> > ClassicLink basics<a name="classiclink-basics"></a> > Control the use of ClassicLink<a name="classiclink-iam"></a>] .

For more information about IAM policies for Amazon EC2, see [IAM policies for Amazon EC2](iam-policies-for-amazon-ec2.md) and [Example policies for working with the AWS CLI or an AWS SDK](aws/EC2/Example policies for working with the AWS CLI or an AWS SDK<a name="ExamplePolicies_EC2"></a>) .
